/*
 * Bot reaction speech pools.
 *
 * Each top-level key is a constant-style category used by bot speech systems. The values are arrays of short chat
 * lines that can be selected randomly when the matching event occurs.
 *
 * DIED:
 * Lines a bot may say shortly after dying and losing items.
 *
 * IMPRESSED:
 * Lines a bot may say when reacting positively to another player, item, achievement, or display of wealth.  Use <name>
 * to reference the name of the person being complimented.
 *
 * LEVEL_UP:
 * Lines a bot may say after it gains a level. Use <skill> and <level> to reference the skill and level that were
 * advanced, respectively.
 *
 * OTHER_DIED:
 * Lines a bot may say after seeing another player die.
 *
 * OTHER_LEVEL_UP:
 * Lines a bot may say after seeing another player gain a level. Use <name> to reference the person levelling up.
 *
 * RARE_DROP:
 * Lines a bot may say after receiving a rare or valuable drop. Use <drop> as the drop-name placeholder.
 *
 * SCAMMED:
 * Lines a bot may say after being scammed. Use <name> as the scammer-name placeholder.
 */
